 succeeded in 963ms:
   1: """SGLang LoRA Tier B pilot driver — m9-c-adopt Phase B Step 5c.
   2: 
   3: Per-rank serialized inference loop against SGLang with LoRA adapter routing.
   4: Ollama-only ``eval_run_golden`` cannot select a LoRA adapter, so this driver
   5: goes straight to the SGLang OpenAI-compatible chat endpoint with
   6: ``model=kant_r{rank}_real`` per Step 4 multi-pin sanity result.
   7: 
   8: Outputs ``raw_dialog`` rows with ``epoch_phase=evaluation`` so the captured
   9: shard never leaks back into training. Per-turn checkpoint resume is keyed on
  10: ``(cycle_idx, stimulus_id)`` so an interrupted run picks up where it left off
  11: without re-firing the prior 100 turns.
  12: 
  13: Scope narrowing (DA-11, Phase B 第 3 セッション):
  14: * Each multi-turn stimulus is folded to a single focal turn (turn_index=0
  15:   only). Rationale: pilot focuses on adapter-conditional Vendi
  16:   diversity / future Big5 ICC, not multi-turn ToM dynamics. Full multi-turn
  17:   采取 deferred to Phase E (A-6 full Tier B 7500 turn).
  18: * No interlocutor; the persona speaks to the stimulus directly.
  19: * SGLang HTTP API only — no MultiBackendChatClient (Phase D scope).
  20: * Big5 ICC + Burrows scoring deferred (separate consumer in Phase B 第 4 セッション).
  21: 
  22: Usage::
  23: 
  24:     python scripts/m9-c-adopt/tier_b_pilot.py \\
  25:         --persona kant --rank 8 --run-idx 0 \\
  26:         --turn-count 300 --cycle-count 6 \\
  27:         --sglang-host http://127.0.0.1:30000 \\
  28:         --output data/eval/m9-c-adopt-tier-b-pilot/kant_r8_run0_stim.duckdb
  29: """
  30: 
  31: from __future__ import annotations
  32: 
  33: import argparse
  34: import dataclasses
  35: import hashlib
  36: import json
  37: import logging
  38: import sys
